Sentencas: Some of the limits on fuel cell development include the issues of hydrogen availability and storage.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol on impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2/YSZ anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Methanol has many advantages as an alternative fuel for fuel cells but depending on the anode composition, the formation of carbon may be a problem.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol on impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2/YSZ anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this paper, the direct utilization of methanol in solid oxide fuel cells with impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2-delta (ZDC)/YSZ anodes was investigated at 1073 K. Performance and stability of these anodes, as measured by steady-state polarization and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy, were improved by the presence of ZDC; although, the deposition of carbon, as detected by scanning electron microscopy and temperature-programmed oxidation analysis, was not entirely avoided.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol on impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2/YSZ anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impact of the carbon, however, was different depending on the anode.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol on impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2/YSZ anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: That is, carbon formation caused the delamination of impregnated Ni/YSZ anodes, while the structural integrity of Ni-ZDC/YSZ anodes was maintained and the cell performance was not negatively impacted.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol on impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2/YSZ anodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Increasing the fuel utilization decreased coking, as predicted by equilibrium calculations.
Titulo: Direct utilization of methanol on impregnated Ni/YSZ and Ni-Zr0.35Ce0.65O2/YSZ anodes for solid oxide fuel cells
